<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06250173 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06250173 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  GILROY; CITY; OFFICE; ELECTION; CANDIDATE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Six candidates will vie for three seats on Gilroy's city council Nov. 5, andtwo candidates are in the race for the mayor's job.;   In the mayoralelection, city council members Pete Valdez, Jr., 46, and Donald Gage, also 46,filed nominating papers by the deadline, according to City Clerk SusanneSteinmetz. Both are midway through third council terms.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  A FULL SLATE IN GILROY8 CANDIDATES VIE FOR CITY OFFICES  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Loser will keep seat; The loser in that race will retain his council seat.The winner's council seat can be filled by council appointment.;   In the racefor three council seats, incumbents Leonard Hale, a 43-year-old accountmanager, and Paul Kloecker, a 56-year-old construction program manager, arebeing challenged by four hopefuls.;   They are Kevin A. &quot;Mike&quot; Gilroy, 55, abusiness consultant and parks and recreation commissioner; Ricardo &quot;Rick&quot;Mello, 55, a businessman and former council and mayoral candidate; Suellen C.Rowlison, 52, a public health nurse and member of the library and culturecommission; and Glenn Shigeru Suyeyasu, 35, a consultant and city planningcommissioner.;   Two incumbents, Councilman Larry Mussallem and Mayor RobertaHughan, are not seeking re-election.;   Democrats and Republicans; Of theeight candidates in the November race, four are registered as Democrats andfour as Republicans, according to the registrar's office.;   Registered asDemocrats are Valdez, Mello, Rowlison and Suyeyasu.;   Registered asRepublicans are Gage, Gilroy, Hale and Kloecker.;   The nominating papers of athird mayoral hopeful who filed by the deadline were rejected by the countyregistrar of voters.;   James Piedad, 21, did not collect the required 20signatures of registered voters, according to Steinmetz. Of the more than 20signatures he gathered, only 14 were of registered voters, she said.;   Thefiling period for candidates ended at 5 p.m. Sept. 3.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  JACK FOLEY, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  South County  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910906  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  September  </MONTH><PG.COL>  1B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  290  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday, September 6, 199100250173,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>